cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper presents two secure two party computation protocols for piecewise function approximation on private data. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses different types of function approximations and their computational complexity. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses communication complexity and the trade-offs between different implementations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as piecewise function approximation is commonly used in machine learning algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the protocols in a secure two party computation setting.
